16:T4c4,This is clearly a complete robotic surgical system (capital equipment platform) from Meril Life Sciences, not an implant or consumable. The specifications describe a comprehensive system with: (1) open console design for surgeon interface, (2) arm cart for instrument manipulation, (3) vision cart with 3D-4K imaging, (4) advanced features including AI planning, fluorescence imaging, tremor filtering, and remote surgery capabilities. Entity type is product_family representing the entire platform. Brand 'MIZZO' is identifiable from the product name. However, without external verification or regulatory documentation (FDA 510k, CE mark details), cannot confirm: exact specialty scope (general surgery, urology, gynecology, etc.), specific competitive positioning, or whether 'Endo 4000' represents a versioning scheme. The 'Advanced' descriptor in original title is marketing language and removed. Material classification is not applicable to capital equipment systems. Sending to review due to: (1) missing brand field in original data, (2) lack of external verification sources, (3) need to confirm multi-specialty scope and specific cleared indications, (4) potential need for component/accessory SKU verification.7:["$","div",null,{"className":"min-h-screen bg-[#0A0A0A] text-white","children":[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org/\",\"@type\":\"Product\",\"name\":\"MIZZO Endo 4000 Advanced Surgical Robotic System\",\"description\":\"Cutting-edge robotic-assisted surgery system with open console design, versatile arm cart, and universal vision cart for enhanced precision and patient outcomes\",\"brand\":{\"@type\":\"Brand\",\"name\":\"Meril\"},\"category\":\"Surgical Robotic Systems\",\"manufacturer\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Meril Life Sciences\"},\"offers\":{\"@type\":\"AggregateOffer\",\"offerCount\":\"1\",\"lowPrice\":\"0\",\"priceCurrency\":\"INR\",\"availability\":\"htt